+## Stavrobot model-control API contract
+
+For conversations created in Stavrobot mode (`conversation_options.type = "stavrobot"` with enabled Stavrobot options), Shelley exposes two conversation-scoped model-control endpoints:
+
+- `GET /api/conversation/{id}/stavrobot/model-control-view`
+  - Returns:
+    - `current`: provider/model state and picker availability
+    - `models`: OpenRouter free-model list when selection is available
+  - Returns `404` if conversation does not exist.
+  - Returns `400` when conversation is not in Stavrobot mode or model-control state cannot be derived.
+
+- `POST /api/conversation/{id}/stavrobot/model-control-apply`
+  - Request body: `{ "model": "<openrouter-model-id>" }`
+  - Returns apply result fields including operation and model transition metadata.
+  - Returns `404` if conversation does not exist.
+  - Returns `400` for invalid request body, missing model, non-Stavrobot conversations, or model-control apply failures.
+
+### UX gating contract for apply
+
+UI behavior for model apply must follow these guardrails:
+
+- Apply controls are shown only for Stavrobot conversations.
+- Apply is disabled unless selected model differs from current model.
+- Apply requires explicit acknowledgement of shared-backend impact before enabling mutation.
+- Acknowledgement is reset on relevant context/selection/view changes.
+- If backend indicates OpenRouter selection is unavailable, UI must present that gating and include backend-provided `reason` when available.
+
+These constraints are intentional to reduce accidental mutations of shared Stavrobot backend model state.
